  {
    "row": 9,
    "rowsha": "8mPbAK9OJrkz0+WowRHGQs6qOZJdgH/4IDN9RG4/Yr4=",
    "originContent": "# The motivation behind it all",
    "translatedContent": "# 这背后的动机"
  },
  {
    "row": 10,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 11,
    "rowsha": "lewxERidl1X+pPasQdQw7/P7wF7tkV646XGIdXc6fVw=",
    "originContent": "What is the point of all this? Well, besides showcasing Bob Ross... I thought it would be clever to have a \"real world\" application to reference when talking architecture. I want something to set a standard, something to clone, something to utilize in all my next .Net Core projects. Like all software (and wine), this will improve with time. ",
    "translatedContent": "这一切的意义何在？嗯，除了展示Bob Ross之外……我认为拥有一个“真实世界”的应用程序作为架构讨论的参考会很聪明。我要做的是设定一个标准，一个可以克隆的模板，一个可以在我所有后续的 .Net Core 项目中使用的东西。就像所有软件（和葡萄酒）一样，这将随着时间的推移而改进。"
  },
  {
    "row": 12,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 13,
    "rowsha": "B3pzLUv4hu9ci4K3YXV844FxFH9yH2ZVRN7UmapxAlU=",
    "originContent": "I also found it fitting, that \"Uncle Bob\" (Robert C. Martin) shares a similar name, and this project makes an attempt to align with his architecture [outlined here on his website.](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2012/08/13/the-clean-architecture.html)",
    "translatedContent": "我还觉得很贴切，“Uncle Bob”（Robert C. Martin）有个相似的名字，而这个项目尝试与他在[他的网站上概述的架构](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2012/08/13/the-clean-architecture.html)保持一致。"
  },
  {
    "row": 14,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 15,
    "rowsha": "Opair+/NAF47qoqKgEFvubmOYYDQRzioQ8pL103EUWA=",
    "originContent": "I also wrote a blog post to pair with it here: [https://www.brandontillman.com/blog/clean-architecture-dotnet](https://www.brandontillman.com/blog/clean-architecture-dotnet)",
    "translatedContent": "我还写了一篇配套博客文章，链接在这里：[https://www.brandontillman.com/blog/clean-architecture-dotnet](https://www.brandontillman.com/blog/clean-architecture-dotnet)"
  },
  {
    "row": 16,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 17,
    "rowsha": "+FabOWY5SUx9FaVaVRjx2QT5vZBEIPAuHuUgDFNOV7s=",
    "originContent": "# Key Points:",
    "translatedContent": "# 关键点："
  },
  {
    "row": 18,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 19,
    "rowsha": "JauUJXKEp4h5WhPGPjinQL2rGWkNoSrHQtuqjy3q0GE=",
    "originContent": "### :trident: N-Tier Architecture",
    "translatedContent": "### :trident: N层架构"
  },
  {
    "row": 20,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 21,
    "rowsha": "Ne9Qr1LfhBIdLVJVXWqKSTLlTyeRdhueiPIrGPcQn24=",
    "originContent": "A 3 layered approach, to set us up for multiple UI's that use the same core business functionality/back-end. ",
    "translatedContent": "一种三层方法，为我们设置多个使用相同核心业务功能/后端的UI。"
  },
  {
    "row": 22,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 23,
    "rowsha": "x1uYrEUOkUA6Lb3A1nI5EbiAUiUo4JjWiVdtQYIpNlg=",
    "originContent": "### :open_file_folder: Separation of Concerns",
    "translatedContent": "### :open_file_folder: 关注点分离"
  },
  {
    "row": 24,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 25,
    "rowsha": "McUE0VYScGcu4UCvjuuJ6REMrSHkZip2mtY8Ia2uZSw=",
    "originContent": "Closely related to the [\"Single Responsibility\"](http://deviq.com/single-responsibility-principle/) principle, Separation of Concerns (SoC) makes your code more maintainable, by not co-locating ideas. When things change, SoC will help ensure your changes are limited to your feature set, and not spread throughout your application.",
    "translatedContent": "与[“单一职责”](http://deviq.com/single-responsibility-principle/)原则密切相关，关注点分离（SoC）使您的代码更易维护，因为它不会将不同的概念混杂在一起。当事物发生变化时，SoC将帮助确保您的更改仅限于您的功能集，而不会波及整个应用程序。"
  },
  {
    "row": 26,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 27,
    "rowsha": "W50b5wRIUn6kDk0jv4KiBGWxuqvFy8tM3sUP+54yZmU=",
    "originContent": "### :droplet: No Leaky Abstractions",
    "translatedContent": "### :droplet: 无泄漏的抽象"
  },
  {
    "row": 28,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 29,
    "rowsha": "UA9EQIcmJgIUYj49yBUtxxRNM4GVbyDKE/P2gs4efco=",
    "originContent": "By using interfaces, we can avoid leaky abstractions, and have better control of how our code is used. On the contrary, consumers of our code don't have to know the implementation details, they can simply use your interfaces/classes.",
    "translatedContent": "通过使用接口，我们可以避免抽象泄漏，更好地控制代码的使用方式。相反，代码的使用者不必了解实现细节，他们只需使用您的接口/类即可。"
  },
  {
    "row": 30,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 31,
    "rowsha": "AEMECMTTU/xgUPuQS3MXlTLO2FkU1rO0oTUV73nybAI=",
    "originContent": "### :microscope: Testable",
    "translatedContent": "### :microscope: 可测试"
  },
  {
    "row": 32,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 33,
    "rowsha": "RsBYx2GQodUzgQN2Ak0WDT0pGpA0TAk8JfIy27cDKhg=",
    "originContent": "Testing code that is tightly coupled is nearly impossible. By following the SOC principal, and using interfaces our code will be easier to rest in result.",
    "translatedContent": "紧耦合的代码几乎无法测试。通过遵循SOC原则并使用接口，我们的代码将更容易进行测试。"
  },
  {
    "row": 34,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 35,
    "rowsha": "tXqaDVipQC435bNRqktlvuRavZXv6DLzMklH26hxUuw=",
    "originContent": "### :electric_plug: Modular",
    "translatedContent": "### :electric_plug: 模块化"
  },
  {
    "row": 36,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 37,
    "rowsha": "yIkRY/duH2Ze2W0hmMt3IHB6p9IVGxiGDGp1yeuGcoI=",
    "originContent": "The code will be easier to modify in the future, because of a few reasons. Separation of concerns allows for fewer changes/testing throughout the application. You can build on specific feature sets, without modifying the rest of the code.",
    "translatedContent": "代码在未来更易于修改，原因有几方面。关注点分离减少了整个应用程序中的更改/测试次数。您可以构建特定的功能集，而无需修改其他代码。"
  },
  {
    "row": 38,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 39,
    "rowsha": "5otxkZedC0VUwSIC58qZJCu7as44fPlGHHEu7tw/syU=",
    "originContent": "### :wrench: Maintainable",
    "translatedContent": "### :wrench: 易维护"
  },
  {
    "row": 40,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 41,
    "rowsha": "R9PXOaRYw0kxey7/SnooQ8/6zSbyx9r2k1crgXtt4Kc=",
    "originContent": "The code will inherently be more maintainable by following Clean Architecture patterns. Other developers will see the benefit of the clean separation, and follow suit.",
    "translatedContent": "通过遵循清洁架构模式，代码本质上将更易于维护。其他开发者会看到这种清晰分离的好处，并效仿之。"
  },
  {
    "row": 42,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
